SIMPLE: magistery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magistery
<hw>Mag"is*ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>magisterium</ets> the office of a chief, president, director,
tutor. See <er>Magistrate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mastery;
powerful medical influence; renowned efficacy; a sovereign remedy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A magisterial injunction.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Brougham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A precipitate; a fine substance
deposited by precipitation; -- applied in old chemistry to certain white
precipitates from metallic solutions; <as>as, <ex>magistery</ex> of
bismuth</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magistracy</ent>⟦br⟧
